      },
      "date": "2016-03-24 15:00:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nPPC64 Builder: build succesful",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9408b30d724e570b58f9220a8a00f668b6cac42a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-03-25 07:46:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHave you done a performance comparison with this patch enabled and disabled to see how much the OST object creation costs?  In theory, there should be no visible performance hit because there are more OSTs than MDTs, and because of precreate, but it would be good to verify this. \n\nIf there is a significant impact from OST precreate then it would be worthwhile to file a ticket to fix it, since this can hurt real world performance, and there is no benefit if the MDT is fast but the OSTs are slow.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "e28c35cd3156c069c280b6488daa127537b15f4f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2016-03-25 08:02:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nmy primary intention was to avoid any overhead (CPU/IO/MEM) related to precreation as i'm running tests on a single node.\n\nclean lustre/ldiskfs, stripes=0:\nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    1 thr    1 create 35510.72 [ 1999.84, 43069.32] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    2 thr    2 create 29457.20 [    0.00, 42998.19] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    4 thr    4 create 25812.10 [ 3999.82, 32998.81] \n\nclean lustre/ldiskfs, stripes=1:\nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    1 thr    1 create 23928.94 [ 8999.60, 33999.05] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    2 thr    2 create 17323.18 [ 2999.83, 27998.07] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    4 thr    4 create 20159.96 [    0.00, 32999.08] \n\nnow the same, but OST precreation is faked\n\nclean lustre/ldiskfs, stripes=0:\nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    1 thr    1 create 37625.63 [  999.93, 47067.56] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    2 thr    2 create 28051.35 [ 2999.79, 41998.15] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    4 thr    4 create 23793.98 [    0.00, 31999.04] \n\nclean lustre/ldiskfs, stripes=1:\nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    1 thr    1 create 29687.65 [ 6999.63, 37069.37] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    2 thr    2 create 27626.70 [ 6999.50, 38998.13] \nmdt 1 file  500000 dir    4 thr    4 create 22838.70 [ 7999.56, 30998.98] \n\nI can confirm that we usually don't wait often for objects and precration on its own is doing well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
